 political thought, Delogu’s book highlights the importance of gender to the functioning of allegory and to the construction of late medieval French identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aFrench literatureyTo 1500xHistory and criticism. 0aGroup identity in literature. 0aSymbolism in literature. 0aWomen in literature. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269006640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442690066423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442690066.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK